-- MORE: Taiwan Central Bank Expects 2012 CPI to Be Within 2%
-- B y   C h i n m e i   S u n g
-- 2012-04-25T02:22:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-25/more-taiwan-central-bank-expects-2012-cpi-to-be-within-2-.html
Taiwan’s consumer prices may rise
within 2% this year, an indication of moderate inflation, Yang
Chin-long, central bank deputy governor, says in reply to
questions from lawmakers in legislature.
* 1Q inflation ’not serious’, Yang says
* DGBAS in Feb. forecast 2012 inflation of 1.46%
